# Semgrep ignore patterns — Story 9.1 (Epic 9 audit baseline)
#
# Semgrep's default `--config auto + p/owasp-top-ten` rulesets flag certain
# patterns inside test fixtures as security errors. Test files contain
# deliberately-crafted dummy secrets / tokens for assertion purposes; flagging
# them yields false positives that drown real findings.
#
# Scope: only test-file patterns are ignored here. Production source and
# config (Dockerfiles, nginx, *.html) remain in scope. The audit baseline
# output (semgrep.json) is the gate input for Story 9.4.

# Frontend test files — vitest + playwright fixtures with TOTP test secrets,
# fake bearer tokens, hard-coded user passwords for mock API responses.
apps/web/src/**/*.test.ts
apps/web/src/**/*.test.tsx
apps/web/tests/**/*.ts
apps/web/tests/**/*.tsx

# Backend test files — pytest fixtures with bcrypt test hashes, JWT secrets,
# bandit B105/B106 false-positive material.
apps/api/tests/**/*.py
workers/render/tests/**/*.py

# Generated / vendored artifacts already covered by --exclude flags but
# duplicated here for safety on direct semgrep invocations.
node_modules/
.venv/
**/dist/
**/build/
**/htmlcov/
**/.pytest_cache/
